# =====================================================================
#  ViMbAdmin queue runner  --  EXAMPLE crontab
# =====================================================================
#  ViMbAdmin's repair / optimize / archive / delete actions are queued in the
#  database (mailbox_task) and carried out by a queue runner that talks to
#  Dovecot over the doveadm HTTP API. The runner must be invoked periodically.
#
#  It can run wherever the ViMbAdmin code + an application.ini pointing at the
#  panel's database live — typically inside the ViMbAdmin container itself. No
#  shell tools, no maildir access and no mail-host checkout are required: the
#  actual mail work (doveadm backup / mailbox delete / fs delete / sync) happens
#  on the Dovecot side over the HTTP API.
#
#  Adjust VIMBADMIN_DIR / the invocation to taste. Dockerised deployments
#  usually run this from the HOST crontab as a `docker exec`, e.g.:
#    */2 * * * *  root  docker exec vimbadmin php /opt/vimbadmin/bin/vimbtool.php -a queue.cli-run
# =====================================================================

SHELL=/bin/sh
MAILTO=postmaster@example.com
VIMBADMIN_DIR=/opt/vimbadmin

# Drain the mailbox-task queue every 2 minutes (caps load via
# queue.runner.max_per_run in application.ini).
*/2 * * * *   root   php ${VIMBADMIN_DIR}/bin/vimbtool.php -a queue.cli-run

# NOTE: mailbox usage for the panel's quota column is fed live by Dovecot's
# quota-clone plugin (see the main README) — no nightly maildir-scan job. There
# is no longer any tar/bzip2 archive cron: archive/delete backups are written by
# the queue (doveadm backup → zstd maildir) and pruned via the Maintenance tab.
